    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen I try to edit my `.editorconfig` file (provided below) in a clean nvim environment, neovim reports the following: \r\n<img width=\"1345\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-10-24 at 09 29 45\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/5877606/367adbc2-90b3-462a-abba-92394fd56bd3\">\r\n\r\nMy editorconfig file:\r\n```ini\r\nroot = true\r\n\r\n[*]\r\ntab_width = 4\r\nindent_size = 4\r\ncharset = \"utf-8\"\r\nend_of_line = \"lf\"\r\nindent_style = \"space\"\r\ninsert_final_newline = true\r\ntrim_trailing_whitespace = true\r\n```\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary>The errors in text form</summary>\r\n  <pre>editorconfig: invalid value for option end_of_line: \"lf\". end_of_line must be one of \"lf\", \"crlf\", or \"cr\"\r\neditorconfig: invalid value for option indent_style: \"space\". indent_style must be either \"tab\" or \"space\"\r\neditorconfig: invalid value for option charset: \"utf-8\". charset must be one of \"utf-8\", \"utf-8-bom\", \"latin1\", \"utf-16be\", or \"utf-16le\"</pre>\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`nvim --clean .editorconfig`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAs I believe my config values are correct, I expect neovim to treat them as such.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.4\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nit has no editorconfig support AFAIK\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.0\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\niterm 2 Build 3.4.21\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew",
